OL,3,C'The sounds my children make are
OL,4,Cliterally crucifying for me'
OL,6,FA mum says the sound of her children's
OL,7,Flaughter "is torturous" for her after
OL,8,Fshe was diagnosed with a debilitating
OL,9,Fand rare hearing disorder.
OL,11,FKaren Cook finds everyday noises like
OL,12,Fthe wind and the trees, running water
OL,13,For even the sound of her children
OL,14,Fplaying causes her crippling pain.
OL,16,FAs a result the 50-year-old from
OL,17,FSouthport spends most days in
OL,18,Fisolation in her bedroom, away from
OL,19,Fher family and watching life pass her
OL,20,Fby from her window.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/10
